pullRequest.body:
Subsets aren't going to have `Nonempty` instances on them, typically, so one would have to manually construct a term of `[Nonempty s]` whenever `PartialHomeomorph.subtypeRestr` is used. Turning this instance argument explicit, `(hs : Nonempty s)` would help us avoid `@PartialHomeomorph.subtypeRestr _ _ _ _` constructions or `haveI : Nonempty ...`.

Its only downstream effect currently is in `ChartedSpace.lean`.

Looks good to me (with the `refine'` change split out). Thank you for doing this.

The changes to `ChartedSpace` show that this is much cleaner. (The upcoming PR #8160 will benefit from this.)
Having to carry around the `hs` argument in all the `subtypeRestr` lemmas is not pretty. Given these are internal changes and this simplifies the outward-facing API, I consider this change a net positive.

As far as I can see, these changes are unrelated to this PR. Can you split them into a different PR?
(Making the change to a line you're modifying anyway is fine (and should perhaps be mentioned in the commit message; I think other lines should be separate.)
You are using the Type version `Nonempty`. Wouldn't it be more natural to use the set version `Set.Nonempty`, as you are dealing with a subset?

This was a conscious choice. When I used `Set.Nonempty`, the proof obligation for that argument when provided with an element of the set is somehow longer. Instead of `⟨x⟩`, you'd have to write `⟨x, x.prop⟩`. Unless I've missed a shorter spelling, I would find the type `Nonempty` easier to use.
ok, that's perfect if it's a deliberate design choice. Maybe add a comment explaining this?
